#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn1.76"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn1.76:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 1 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 1 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.76:0.2"
msgid "8. Chetvāvagga "
msgstr "8. Incinerated "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn1.76:0.3"
msgid "76. Najīratisutta "
msgstr "76. Getting Old "

#. HTML: </h1></div><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.97, sc1
msgctxt "sn1.76:1.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ jīrati kiṃ na jīrati, "
msgstr "“What gets old, what doesn’t get old? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.76:1.2"
msgid "kiṃsu uppathoti vuccati; "
msgstr "What’s called a deviation? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.76:1.3"
msgid "Kiṃsu dhammānaṃ paripantho, "
msgstr "What’s a roadblock for skillful qualities? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.76:1.4"
msgid "kiṃsu rattindivakkhayo; "
msgstr "What is ending day and night? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.76:1.5"
msgid "Kiṃ malaṃ brahmacariyassa, "
msgstr "What’s the stain of celibacy? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.76:1.6"
msgid "kiṃ sinānamanodakaṃ. "
msgstr "What’s the waterless bath? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn1.76:2.1"
msgid "Kati lokasmiṃ chiddāni, "
msgstr "How many holes are there in the world, "

# NOTE: BB read citta, but this is certainly wrong. At AN 10.73 we have ālasyaṃ anuṭṭhānaṃ bhogānaṃ paripantho, which must surely have the same meaning. The point is that the question pitches at a worldly level, and the Buddha raises it up, as per usual in the sagathavagga. This makes the whole metaphor of “holes “and” remain” far more straightforward.
#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: vittaṃ → cittaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn1.76:2.2"
msgid "yattha vittaṃ na tiṭṭhati; "
msgstr "where one’s wealth leaks out? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.76:2.3"
msgid "Bhagavantaṃ puṭṭhumāgamma, "
msgstr "We’ve come to ask the Buddha; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.76:2.4"
msgid "kathaṃ jānemu taṃ mayan”ti. "
msgstr "how are we to understand this?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn1.76:3.1"
msgid "“Rūpaṃ jīrati maccānaṃ, "
msgstr "“The physical form of mortals gets old, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.76:3.2"
msgid "nāmagottaṃ na jīrati; "
msgstr "but their name and clan don’t. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.76:3.3"
msgid "Rāgo uppathoti vuccati. "
msgstr "Lust is called a deviation, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn1.76:4.1"
msgid "Lobho dhammānaṃ paripantho, "
msgstr "and greed obstructs skillful qualities. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.76:4.2"
msgid "Vayo rattindivakkhayo; "
msgstr "Youth is ending day and night. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.76:4.3"
msgid "Itthī malaṃ brahmacariyassa, "
msgstr "Women are the stain of celibacy, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.76:4.4"
msgid "Etthāyaṃ sajjate pajā; "
msgstr "to which this generation clings. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.76:4.5"
msgid "Tapo ca brahmacariyañca, "
msgstr "Austerity and celibacy "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.76:4.6"
msgid "Taṃ sinānamanodakaṃ. "
msgstr "are the waterless bath. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.98, sc5
msgctxt "sn1.76:5.1"
msgid "Cha lokasmiṃ chiddāni, "
msgstr "There are six holes in the world, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.76:5.2"
msgid "yattha vittaṃ na tiṭṭhati; "
msgstr "where one’s wealth leaks out: "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Ālasyañca → ālassañca (bj, pts2) | alassañca (pts1)
msgctxt "sn1.76:5.3"
msgid "Ālasyañca pamādo ca, "
msgstr "laziness and negligence, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.76:5.4"
msgid "anuṭṭhānaṃ asaṃyamo; "
msgstr "lack of initiative and lack of restraint, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: tandī → tandi (bj)
msgctxt "sn1.76:5.5"
msgid "Niddā tandī ca te chidde, "
msgstr "sleepiness and sloth. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.76:5.6"
msgid "sabbaso taṃ vivajjaye”ti. "
msgstr "You should completely get rid of these holes!”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
